OL,6,FThe former car salesman, dressed in a
OL,7,Fgrey suit and striped tie, sat in the
OL,8,Fdock as the judge delivered his
OL,9,Fremarks.
OL,11,FAt the conclusion of the hearing, a
OL,12,Fnumber of the victims and their
OL,13,Ffamilies shouted abuse at MacCormack
OL,14,Ffrom the public gallery as he was led
OL,15,Fout of the court. He did not react to
OL,16,Fshouting.
OL,18,FThe prosecution of MacCormack followed
OL,19,Fan investigation by the PSNI's modern
OL,20,Fslavery and human trafficking unit.
